DIV1.P:
The Prisoner had little to say in his De∣fence;
he endeavour'd to prove himself Alibi;
so that the Trial turn'd upon this single Que∣stion,
whether the said Timothy Trim and
Jack, were the same Person? which was
prov'd by such plain Tokens, and particu∣larly
by a Mole under the left Pap, that


there was no withstanding the Evidence;
therefore the Worshipful Mr. Justice com∣mitted
him, in order to his Tryal.

SP.P:
Thou hast so many If's and And's;
prithee dispatch; it might have been over be∣fore
this time.

